headline: Watch: Navy Seals Unite to Bring Down Nancy Pelosi in Powerful New Video
author: Missy Crane
sentences:
MORE NEWS: Pelosi’s House of Cards Just Took Two More Brutal Hits… Her Kingdom is Collapsing
The ad features the following six SEAL veterans running in this year’s midterms: Morgan Luttrell (running in Texas’ eighth district), Brady Duke (running in Florida’s seventh district), Eli Crane (running in Arizona’s second district), Derrick Van Orden (running in Wisconsin’s third district), Ed Thelander (running in Maine’s first district), and Ryan Zinke (running in Montana’s first district).

Breitbart reported that a PAC supporting six Navy SEAL combat veterans running for Congress this year released a hard-hitting ad highlighting the sacrifices these men made to protect America “from enemies all over the world” and their determination in November’s midterm elections to beat the “one grave threat left to defeat”: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi (D-CA) and the Democrats who control Congress.

The ad shows black and white photographs of these men from their days serving the United States in combat zones around the world, as a voice over narration states:
They took a blood oath to defend America.
A new Rasmussen poll revealed Republicans are currently enjoying a nine-point lead over Dems in a generic congressional ballot.
“Now they have one grave threat left to defeat,” the voice over concludes, revealing a photograph in color of Nancy Pelosi.

Promoted Content
It’s all hands on deck to take down Nancy Pelosi and retake the House (and Senate).
These former Navy SEALs have protected America from enemies all over the world.
They know that our enemies are no match for their strength and their courage.
And right now, a group of Navy Seals has come together to do exactly that.
They’ve got Pelosi in their sights and they’re on a mission to remove her.
This greatly reduces Pelosi’s chance of holding onto the speaker’s gavel.

Pelosi’s in big trouble.
They understand that the only easy day was yesterday.
A record number 28 House Dems are calling it quits.
They see the writing on the wall.
